26/09/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The OSCE mission in Albania is holding a forum Friday (26 September) to train and co-ordinate the efforts of local election observers.The observers, mostly NGO representatives, will sign a joint statement confirming their participation in the process ahead of the 12 October vote.
In other news, the US Peace Corps is returning to Albania after a six-year break. 
US Ambassador James Jeffrey welcomed the first group of 32 volunteers Thursday. 
The Corps pulled out in 1997 amid social unrest fueled by failed pyramid schemes. 
(OSCE Web site, ATA, BBC - 25/09/03)
